	<key>description</key>
	<string>Disables auto shift after deleting characters.

Useful for anyone who uses "Auto-Capitalization" @Settings -&gt; General -&gt; Keyboards but are annoyed by stock iOS capitalizing replacement characters when deleting text (i.e. when backspace/deleting two characters in the text "aBc", the new replacement character for "B" is capitalized).  With this patch enabled, new text replacements will be lowercase.

[v.1] Tested with an iPad mini 4 on 10.2.  Requested by r/jailbreak user /u/clstudios.  (11-21-17)

